tyle=3D"margin:10px 0">OK it was a pretty crappy call but it contained lots=
 of very positive nuggets. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Profits from sell=
ing cars stayed about the same, even though more buyers are choosing the Fu=
ll Self-Driving (FSD) software upgrade. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Ener=
gy Storage Profits were lower than normal because of some temporary issues.=
 They should settle back around a healthy 25% going forward.</p><p style=3D=
"margin:10px 0">Robotaxi (Self-Driving Taxi) Progress =E2=80=94 some truly =
impressive updates:</p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Tesla has already=
 completed more than 380,000 miles of unsupervised Robotaxi driving (no hum=
an safety driver in the car) with zero notable incidents. This is one of th=
e strongest real-world safety proofs Tesla has ever shared for fully driver=
less operation.</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Testing miles are gr=
owing fast =E2=80=94 by double-digit percentages every week. To support thi=
s pace, Tesla expects to have roughly 5,000 cars in the Robotaxi test fleet=
 by the end of the year.</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">The current=
 test fleet (using both the new dedicated Cybercab and regular Model Y vehi=
cles) is already running early versions of the next big software update: FS=
D Version 15. They're actively improving it with several planned tracks.</p=
></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Tesla has no plans to partner with Ube=
r or Lyft. They will run their own independent Robotaxi network.  </p></li>=
<li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">FSD is already helping sell more new Teslas =
in the U.S. and other places where it=E2=80=99s approved for use.</p></li><=
/ul><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Upgrades for Older Cars are still planned if=
 they had FSD. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Tesla Semi Truck</p><ul><li><=
p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Work on making the Semi self-driving (FSD for tru=
cks) is expected to start toward the end of 2026 or early 2027. They=E2=80=
=99re being careful not to rush it or distract from perfecting safety on pa=
ssenger cars and the Cybercab first.</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0"=
>Production of the Semi trucks themselves is still ramping up slowly.</p></=
li></ul><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Optimus Humanoid Robot</p><ul><li><p sty=
le=3D"margin:10px 0">Production of the Optimus robot will also ramp up very=
 slowly at first. We know but the new line is impressive. </p></li><li><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:10px 0">Optimus is expected to be special: it should be the =
only robot that can truly =E2=80=9Csee=E2=80=9D and understand the world ar=
ound it (using advanced vision) and perform complex tasks the way a human w=
ould.</p></li></ul><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Major New Factory: Terafab</p=
><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Tesla will soon make a big announcement about T=
erafab (or share more details on its location/plans). This is a massive new=
 project. It will combine chip design, manufacturing, memory, and packaging=
 under one roof =E2=80=94 critical for powering self-driving tech, Optimus,=
 and AI training. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Solar and Energy Storage</=
p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Tesla=E2=80=99s solar panel manufactur=
ing factory is coming online sooner than previously expected. It will mainl=
y supply panels for Tesla=E2=80=99s own large solar projects and =E2=80=9CT=
esla farms.=E2=80=9D</p></li></ul><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Memory and Mic=
ron</p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Supply Chain =E2=80=94 Tesla has =
secured a significant supply of important memory chips from Micron at good =
